1
00:00:22,314 --> 00:00:23,482
<i>What do you think about Teo, love?</i>

2
00:00:23,566 --> 00:00:25,234
<i>Kind of weird earlier</i>
<i>because he was calling me...</i>

3
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:27,027
- Yana Kassir.
- Doppelgangers.

4
00:00:27,111 --> 00:00:27,945
But don't worry.

5
00:00:28,028 --> 00:00:28,904
I don't sense anything bad about him.

6
00:00:28,988 --> 00:00:30,072
I need a favor.

7
00:00:30,156 --> 00:00:32,366
<i>Can you get</i>
<i>a death certificate or police report?</i>

8
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:33,951
Anything that proves
that Yana is really dead.

9
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:35,828
The police found Yana's body.

10
00:00:35,911 --> 00:00:36,746
- <i>Papa!</i>
- Why?

11
00:00:36,829 --> 00:00:38,038
My passport is missing.

12
00:00:38,122 --> 00:00:39,248
I have something to show you.

13
00:00:39,331 --> 00:00:42,001
She was a terrible person.
I despise her, ma'am.

14
00:00:42,084 --> 00:00:44,253
You should get rid of
all your memories of her.

15
00:00:44,336 --> 00:00:46,464
That job that you gave him?
That was a huge blessing for us.

16
00:00:46,547 --> 00:00:48,507
I hope we can find luck with you.

17
00:00:48,591 --> 00:00:49,925
That is, if he does his job well.

18
00:00:50,009 --> 00:00:50,968
I said, faster!

19
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:52,553
- Sir, this is dangerous.
- <i>Don't stop.</i>

20
00:00:52,636 --> 00:00:54,388
- <i>Overspeeding.</i>
- Sorry for the trouble.

21
00:00:54,472 --> 00:00:56,348
If you can't obey my orders,
then you're fired.

22
00:00:56,432 --> 00:00:57,516
Ma'am!

23
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,517
<i>What the hell is going on?</i>

24
00:00:58,601 --> 00:00:59,852
Ace! Ace!

25
00:00:59,935 --> 00:01:00,853
Get him out of here!

26
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:02,480
- Ace, let me explain!
- Ace!

27
00:01:03,105 --> 00:01:05,608
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

28
00:02:24,228 --> 00:02:26,564

That lawyer is a jealous man, huh?

29
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:27,565
Goodness.

30
00:02:27,648 --> 00:02:29,149
I didn't do anything wrong.

31
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:31,360
Yeah, that might be true,

32
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:33,654
but to him,
you were doing something wrong.

33
00:02:33,737 --> 00:02:35,281
But don't worry, I got you.

34
00:02:35,865 --> 00:02:37,366
I'll find you another job.

35
00:02:37,449 --> 00:02:39,076
- Teo.
Pa?

36
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,703
You're looking for another job?

37
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:51,964
What happened to your face?

38
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:53,757
Didn't I tell you to keep your cool?

39
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:56,176
Sir Ace hit me.

40
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:58,137
He thought
I was taking advantage of his wife.

41
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,680
But that wasn't what happened.

42
00:03:00,264 --> 00:03:01,515
He fired me on the spot.

43
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:02,850


44
00:03:05,853 --> 00:03:07,062
- Hey, hey.
Oh?

45
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:09,440
It's Sir Steven,
the butler at the mansion.

46
00:03:09,523 --> 00:03:10,858
Sir Ace wants to talk to me.

47
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:12,151
Probably to give me my job back.

48
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:13,861

There we go!

49
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:16,572
- I'll go get changed.
Good luck!

50
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:19,617
Sir...

51
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:21,660
Teo.

52
00:03:22,745 --> 00:03:24,914
I'm sorry, I didn't have
the chance to explain.

53
00:03:24,997 --> 00:03:27,374
I just went here to put something
in the storage room.

54
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:29,668
She walked in and slipped.

55
00:03:29,752 --> 00:03:31,962
I caught her just as you walked in.

56
00:03:33,631 --> 00:03:35,341
You know I wouldn't do that, sir.

57
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:37,259
I owe you a lot.

58
00:03:37,343 --> 00:03:39,219
I can't afford to lose this job.

59
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:41,931
My family relies on me.

60
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,685
I've talked with Gem.

61
00:03:47,937 --> 00:03:49,188
She told me the same thing.

62
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:55,653

I hope it doesn't happen again.

63
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:56,820
Otherwise...

64
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:01,700
you know me well.

65
00:04:02,368 --> 00:04:03,494
Good.

66
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:06,747
Now, go back to work.

67
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:07,957
Thank you, sir.

68
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:11,752
I want to use this one. Get it ready.

69
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:14,922
Go on.

70
00:04:16,674 --> 00:04:18,133


71
00:04:32,147 --> 00:04:33,232
Feeling better?

72
00:04:34,149 --> 00:04:37,778
Of course. Who wouldn't feel special?

73
00:04:37,861 --> 00:04:41,824
I'm a walking 3.4-million woman today.

74
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:43,492


75
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:47,830
I already requested
the speedy release of your passport.

76
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:50,499
Papa talked to
the ambassador about your visas and all,

77
00:04:50,582 --> 00:04:53,002
so, we're still able to go,

78
00:04:53,085 --> 00:04:54,628
but with just a bit of delay.

79
00:04:54,712 --> 00:04:55,546
Perfect.

80
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:59,174

Teo, has Steven handed you your salary?

81
00:04:59,258 --> 00:05:02,177
Yes, sir. Thank you for the extra.

82
00:05:02,261 --> 00:05:03,470
Go home early today.

83
00:05:03,554 --> 00:05:04,930
Treat your family.

84
00:05:05,431 --> 00:05:07,141

I'm taking my wife out tonight.

85
00:05:07,224 --> 00:05:08,642
-
Just the two of us.

86
00:05:09,852 --> 00:05:11,228
Where are we going?

87
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:13,605
Well, you know,
one of your favorite restaurants.

88
00:05:13,689 --> 00:05:16,150
- Oh, that's so exciting.

89
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:20,571
I'm home, Pa.

90
00:05:20,654 --> 00:05:22,364
Huh. That's a lot of stuff.

91
00:05:22,448 --> 00:05:24,616
Well, it's my first salary anyway.

92
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,744
Save some for yourself.

93
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:28,328


94
00:05:30,289 --> 00:05:32,541
I got the roof and the gutter fixed.

95
00:05:32,624 --> 00:05:34,710
I'm sick of it raining inside the house.

96
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:37,671
Oh, thank God.
It's almost the rainy season, too.

97
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:43,677
Wow!

98
00:05:43,761 --> 00:05:45,012
There's so many groceries!

99
00:05:45,095 --> 00:05:46,930
How are your remedial classes?

100
00:05:47,014 --> 00:05:48,307
I'm doing good.

101
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:50,642
I got perfect scores on my quizzes.

102
00:05:50,726 --> 00:05:52,770
- Oh.
And to be honest,

103
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,688
I find our lessons easy.

104
00:05:54,772 --> 00:05:57,441
It'll be a breeze to go back to school.

105
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:58,776
That's good.

106
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:01,403
- I'll be upstairs. Okay.
Okay, okay.

107
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:08,160
Pa, get dressed.

108
00:06:08,744 --> 00:06:10,871
We're going to get you a prosthetic leg.

109
00:06:12,122 --> 00:06:14,917

So, the first step is making the mold

110
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,586
with plasters or 3-D scans.

111
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:20,047
It's to get an exact fit for your socket.

112
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:22,174
Then, we're going to select the materials.

113
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:24,885
We have basic ones and advanced ones.

114
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:26,970
Next is the trial fitting.

115
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:30,015
There, we'll make adjustments
if necessary.

116
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:34,394
We're so close
to getting you a new leg, Pa.

117
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:43,695
- Papa?
Teo.

118
00:06:45,531 --> 00:06:47,032
You're fired!

119
00:06:47,783 --> 00:06:50,285
- But why, sir?
Pa, what's this?

120
00:06:50,369 --> 00:06:52,955
I was able to obtain
his records from Morocco.

121
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:56,166
That man was convicted
of murder and robbery.

122
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:59,128
Pa! Let's not play around
with his employment.

123
00:06:59,211 --> 00:07:01,505
You let a criminal into our home.

124
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:03,674
You put our family in danger!

125
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,385

Haven't you learned anything?

126
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:09,346
I knew Teo went to jail!

127
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:12,975


128
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:16,979
Teo submitted his
police clearance and other clearances.

129
00:07:17,813 --> 00:07:19,356

He had a physical assault case,

130
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,607
but that was dropped.

131
00:07:20,691 --> 00:07:23,527
I didn't tell you about Morocco,
'cause that was in the past!

132
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,320
He's a convict!

133
00:07:25,404 --> 00:07:27,531
Haven't you learned anything
from our past traumas?

134
00:07:27,614 --> 00:07:29,283
People deserve to have second chances, Pa!

135
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:30,659
As they say...

136
00:07:30,742 --> 00:07:32,995
Every saint has a past,
and every sinner has a future.

137
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:34,037
Bullshit!

138
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:35,664
Justice without mercy is cruelty, Pa!

139
00:07:35,747 --> 00:07:37,791
Jurisprudence is not measured

140
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:40,169
by merely passing the Bar,

141
00:07:40,252 --> 00:07:42,546
but by presiding over it!

142
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:46,800
You still have a long way to go
before you attain judicial wisdom.

143
00:07:46,884 --> 00:07:49,219
You have yet to prove yourself to me!

144
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:19,249
If it's not an issue with Ace...

145
00:08:19,917 --> 00:08:21,376
So come on.

146
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:25,172
It's as if we don't employ people
with criminal records.

147
00:08:28,926 --> 00:08:30,802
Maybe we could use him.

148
00:08:30,886 --> 00:08:32,054
Use him for what?

149
00:08:32,721 --> 00:08:35,724
He's got a criminal record.
He has nowhere to go.

150
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:40,062
I have a bad feeling about this.

151
00:08:40,145 --> 00:08:42,814
People like that are treated as rejects.

152
00:08:42,898 --> 00:08:44,816
Society despises them.

153
00:08:45,901 --> 00:08:48,862
But if you're kind to them
and you treat them well...

154
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:53,116
they'll serve you with
a loyalty you'll never find anywhere else.

155
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:55,702
Come on, love.

156
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:01,959
Why did you lie to me?

157
00:09:03,377 --> 00:09:05,963
Why didn't you tell me
about your other conviction?

158
00:09:06,755 --> 00:09:08,799
I didn't mean to lie, sir.

159
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:11,760
I just forgot to tell you
about my case in Morocco.

160
00:09:12,970 --> 00:09:14,429
Ah.

161
00:09:14,513 --> 00:09:16,139
So, you're a lawyer now?

162
00:09:16,223 --> 00:09:18,767
I just needed a job, sir.

163
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:22,354
When you made the offer,
I couldn't say no.

164
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:26,233
But wherever I go and whatever I do,

165
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:28,485
I know, and I'm confident

166
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,904
that now my conscience is clear.

167
00:09:31,947 --> 00:09:34,449
They gave me a royal pardon.

168
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:38,036
They saw that my association
with the case wasn't that strong,

169
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,663
so they let me go.

170
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:43,166
But then again, I can't blame you, sir,

171
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:45,168
if you want to fire me for real.

172
00:09:45,252 --> 00:09:46,253
That's right.

173
00:09:46,837 --> 00:09:48,422
I should, and I will.

174
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:53,051
But I will not give my father
any satisfaction

175
00:09:53,135 --> 00:09:55,053
that I was fooled by someone like you.

176
00:09:55,637 --> 00:09:57,097
I don't lose, Teo.

177
00:09:57,848 --> 00:09:58,974
Not to you,

178
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:01,059
not to anyone.

179
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,604
I was mistakenly charged
and convicted in Morocco.

180
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:08,525
I'm a victim, sir, not a criminal.

181
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:12,070
What else are you not telling me?

182
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:15,741
Nothing else, sir.

183
00:10:26,335 --> 00:10:27,377
It's so good!

184
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:29,254
- Yeah?
- Yes. Thank you.

185
00:10:29,338 --> 00:10:30,964
Boss, two<i> kwek-kweks</i>, please.

186
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:32,507
It's okay, huh?

187
00:10:33,091 --> 00:10:34,760
Yes.

188
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:39,723
Stay in love.

189
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:42,684
<i>Yes, Papa. And I'm sorry</i>
<i>I can't bring you to the airport today.</i>

190
00:10:42,768 --> 00:10:44,061
<i>No problem.</i>

191
00:10:49,524 --> 00:10:50,901
Thanks. It's delicious.

192
00:10:52,903 --> 00:10:54,321
Oh, thank God.

193
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:34,903
Thank you.

194
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:36,988
Boss, mind if I ask you something?

195
00:11:37,072 --> 00:11:38,615
I'm looking for a foreigner.

196
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,617
I saw him buying here yesterday.

197
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,537
Well, a lot of foreigners buy here
every day.

198
00:11:44,121 --> 00:11:46,790
He's Spanish. Jorge Ybañez.

199
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,292
This man.

200
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:51,753
Ah, yes.

201
00:11:51,837 --> 00:11:54,756
He often buys here,
but I don't know his name.

202
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:57,092
He's Spanish, but he speaks Tagalog.

203
00:11:57,676 --> 00:12:00,804
That building
where all the foreigners live,

204
00:12:00,887 --> 00:12:01,805
that's where he stays.

205
00:12:01,888 --> 00:12:02,806
Why do you ask?

206
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:05,892
I'm just looking for him
for some unpaid debt.

207
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:07,686
Don't tell him about this, would you?

208
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:09,563
He might run off again.

209
00:12:09,646 --> 00:12:11,481
- Okay.
- Thank you.

210
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:45,724
Cold drinks!

211
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:17,714
Hello, sir?

212
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:19,216
Where are you?

213
00:13:19,716 --> 00:13:21,593
Go back to the office.

214
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:23,220
Sir Ace is about to leave.

215
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:24,679
Okay, sir. I'm on my way.

216
00:13:24,763 --> 00:13:26,097
<i> Hurry up.</i>

217
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:34,648
Did Teo drive you here?

218
00:13:34,731 --> 00:13:35,982
Yes, love.

219
00:13:36,942 --> 00:13:39,778
Love, can you send him home?

220
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:41,446
I have my car.
I can drive you.

221
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:44,533
I just don't feel comfortable
around him.

222
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:46,284
And I don't think
you should be with him either.

223
00:13:48,954 --> 00:13:51,414
- Do you want me to fire him?
- Yes, please!

224
00:13:51,498 --> 00:13:52,415
Then go ahead.

225
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:55,168
You make all the decisions.
You're the one who knows better, right?

226
00:13:56,419 --> 00:13:57,921
You think I didn't think this through

227
00:13:58,004 --> 00:14:00,298
and decided that keeping him
was the better option?

228
00:14:00,382 --> 00:14:02,050
I didn't mean it that way.

229
00:14:04,970 --> 00:14:06,388
Let's not talk about him anymore.

230
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:07,764
I was trying not to linger
on this issue,

231
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:08,848
but you keep bringing it up.

232
00:14:11,393 --> 00:14:12,602
Sorry.

233
00:14:13,812 --> 00:14:14,938
Thank you.

234
00:14:17,816 --> 00:14:18,942
Let's just eat.

235
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:21,278
Teo stays, okay?

236
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:22,445
I'm sorry.

237
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:25,699
Do you know what happens
if you end up in jail?

238
00:14:27,158 --> 00:14:29,619
When you don't even know
if you'll make it out alive.

239
00:14:30,662 --> 00:14:32,789
That quiet anger
that's building inside of you...

240
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,082
it changes you.

241
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,085
And that's what happened to Teo,
and I understand him.

242
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:45,302
Waiter?

243
00:14:46,595 --> 00:14:47,596
Yes, sir?

244
00:14:48,763 --> 00:14:49,889
It's dirty.

245
00:14:51,141 --> 00:14:53,727
- I'll replace it, sir.
- You can use mine, love.

246
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:56,354
Replace everything!

247
00:14:56,438 --> 00:14:59,065
Plates, glasses... everything! Now!

248
00:14:59,316 --> 00:15:00,984
All right, sir.

249
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:17,500
Psst.

250
00:15:18,335 --> 00:15:19,336
Talk about short notice.

251
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:23,006
Good thing I'm single,
or you'd have no one to bond with.

252
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:27,260
You're the one who won't stop bugging me.

253
00:15:27,344 --> 00:15:30,805
I mean...
this job is seriously driving me crazy.

254
00:15:30,889 --> 00:15:32,891
There are so many events!

255
00:15:32,974 --> 00:15:35,226
The deliverables are making my head spin.

256
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,979
But it's exciting.

257
00:15:38,063 --> 00:15:40,273
How about you?

258
00:15:40,357 --> 00:15:43,276
I told you to just tell them
you were locked up in Morocco.

259
00:15:44,194 --> 00:15:48,907
And now... the ex-judge
and Madam are fighting.

260
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:51,034
And then Miss Gem?

261
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:53,119
Well, they're packing now.

262
00:15:53,203 --> 00:15:54,913
Their move to the States
is happening sooner.

263
00:15:55,497 --> 00:15:59,209
When will they be leaving?
What will happen to me if they leave?

264
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:00,752
Well, that's going to be a problem.

265
00:16:00,835 --> 00:16:02,295
You'd better clear that up with Sir.

266
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,506
All right, thank you.

267
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:06,049
No problem.

268
00:16:06,758 --> 00:16:09,678
Maybe we're brought to the same place

269
00:16:09,761 --> 00:16:10,929
so we can always...

270
00:16:11,638 --> 00:16:13,640
look out for one another.

271
00:16:13,723 --> 00:16:16,059
- Hey, Larajean.
- What?

272
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:29,739
Larajean. Mama is calling you.

273
00:16:29,823 --> 00:16:31,074
Yes, Ma'am Gem.

274
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:33,618
- Ma'am.
- Excuse me, ma'am.

275
00:16:33,702 --> 00:16:35,245
Do you need me
to take you somewhere?

276
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,080
Will we use this car or Sir Ace's?

277
00:16:37,163 --> 00:16:38,957
I'll just use the other one.

278
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,126
I didn't realize
your father was still here, ma'am.

279
00:16:42,544 --> 00:16:44,337
I actually saw him.

280
00:16:44,421 --> 00:16:46,548
Didn't we just drop him off
at the airport the other day?

281
00:16:47,132 --> 00:16:49,426
- What?
- Unit 1538.

282
00:16:50,719 --> 00:16:53,263
Encina Heights, Los Olivos.

283
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:56,141
That's where I saw him.

284
00:16:56,224 --> 00:16:58,059
What the hell are you talking about?

285
00:16:58,852 --> 00:17:00,770
That I'm the girl that you're saying?

286
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:02,147
Why? Am I wrong?

287
00:17:02,731 --> 00:17:04,482
You and your delusions.

288
00:17:04,566 --> 00:17:06,901
I don't have anything
to prove to you, Teo.

289
00:17:06,985 --> 00:17:08,945
You know what I feel for you?

290
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:10,447
Pity.

291
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:14,784
Because Ace hurt you,
and I feel guilty about it.

292
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:17,871
So, here.

293
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:24,085
<i>My daughter! How are you?</i>

294
00:17:24,169 --> 00:17:25,545
Hello, Papa!

295
00:17:25,628 --> 00:17:27,088
<i>You called?</i>

296
00:17:32,218 --> 00:17:33,386
<i>I am with your mother.</i>

297
00:17:33,470 --> 00:17:34,846
Can I talk to her?

298
00:17:34,929 --> 00:17:36,890
<i>She's sleeping.</i>

299
00:17:36,973 --> 00:17:39,309
<i>We just came back from her dialysis.</i>

300
00:17:50,278 --> 00:17:51,613
How was your flight, Papa?

301
00:17:51,696 --> 00:17:52,864
<i>It was okay.</i>

302
00:17:54,491 --> 00:17:57,577
<i>Your mom really liked your gift.</i>

303
00:17:57,660 --> 00:17:59,662
<i>She hopes to see you soon.</i>

304
00:17:59,746 --> 00:18:01,331
Me too, Papa.

305
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:04,125
Glad to hear she likes it.

306
00:18:04,209 --> 00:18:06,753
I'll just call back later. Love you, Papa.

307
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:17,514
Anger is like fire.

308
00:18:19,307 --> 00:18:21,684
Wild, it burns everything.

309
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:25,522
But with purpose...

310
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:27,941
it becomes power.

311
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,828
Whatever it is you're talking about...

312
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:41,996
I don't care.

313
00:18:44,499 --> 00:18:46,709
Don't wait for my pity to run out, Teo.

314
00:18:46,793 --> 00:18:48,002
Obviously...

315
00:18:49,587 --> 00:18:50,839
you're struggling.

316
00:18:51,422 --> 00:18:53,216
And I know you're working for your family.

317
00:18:53,842 --> 00:18:55,760
You're hanging by a thin rope.

318
00:18:56,469 --> 00:18:58,304
One mistake and you're done.

319
00:18:58,930 --> 00:19:00,723
If that happens,

320
00:19:01,558 --> 00:19:03,685
you'll just be another loser.

321
00:19:23,913 --> 00:19:26,124
Go slowly.

322
00:19:26,207 --> 00:19:28,418
There we go.

323
00:19:28,501 --> 00:19:31,337
Oops. Just remember that...

324
00:19:31,421 --> 00:19:33,047
- This is great!
- ...you should balance first

325
00:19:33,131 --> 00:19:34,215
before you take a step.

326
00:19:34,299 --> 00:19:35,383
This'll only take a couple of sessions.

327
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:38,136
You'll get used to
being without your crutches soon.

328
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,306
Nice one, Uncle Alonzo.

329
00:19:41,389 --> 00:19:43,850
You'll be the first one out
during a gambling raid!

330
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:44,976
Shut up!

331
00:19:45,059 --> 00:19:47,061
You look more handsome, Pa!

332
00:19:47,145 --> 00:19:48,563
Really?

333
00:19:48,646 --> 00:19:50,940
You're walking straight again.

334
00:19:51,024 --> 00:19:52,191
Teo.

335
00:19:52,275 --> 00:19:53,484
Thank you very much.

336
00:19:54,152 --> 00:19:55,361
I know...

337
00:19:55,445 --> 00:19:57,071
you've got a lot of bills to pay.

338
00:19:57,655 --> 00:19:59,365
And then there's me...
just adding to your burden.

339
00:19:59,949 --> 00:20:01,326
You deserve it, Pa.

340
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:03,828
You can go out and have fun with us now.

341
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:05,872
I'd love to invite you

342
00:20:05,955 --> 00:20:09,208
to Madam Katarina and Miss Gem's
new collection launch.

343
00:20:09,918 --> 00:20:11,294
- I'm serious.
- Oh, no. No, thanks.

344
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,714
- Wait, you're there too?
- Yeah.

345
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:15,798
I might be there too!

346
00:20:15,882 --> 00:20:19,052
They invited all of their scholars, so...

347
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:21,387
- I have to show up.
- Do you need to go?

348
00:20:22,639 --> 00:20:23,932
Yes, Teo.

349
00:20:24,724 --> 00:20:27,352
- Well, I didn't want to, but--
- Then don't go.

350
00:20:27,936 --> 00:20:29,437
Tell them you're sick.

351
00:20:30,396 --> 00:20:31,314
Don't go.

352
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:34,359
Uncle Alonzo...

353
00:20:34,442 --> 00:20:36,903
Pa, I'll just pay for this.

354
00:20:36,986 --> 00:20:38,279
Looks like that's going to take a while.

355
00:20:38,363 --> 00:20:39,864
I'll just go to the bathroom.

356
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:41,950
I'll go with you, Teo.

357
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:44,744
- Adjust it, please. Larajean?
- Yes, Uncle Alonzo?

358
00:20:44,827 --> 00:20:46,245
What's wrong?

359
00:20:46,996 --> 00:20:49,457
You're working with Teo
at the mansion, right?

360
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:52,669
Is he telling you something
about a girl named "Yana"?

361
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:54,295
Yana?

362
00:20:54,379 --> 00:20:56,965
The one who scammed him in Morocco?

363
00:20:58,549 --> 00:21:00,385
Nothing, really. Why?

364
00:21:00,468 --> 00:21:02,845
It's about...

365
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:04,472
Gem Verona.

366
00:21:04,555 --> 00:21:07,684
Gem Verona. Sir Ace's wife.

367
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:10,645
Apparently, those two look identical.

368
00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:14,232
- She transformed?
- Like a chameleon.

369
00:21:15,441 --> 00:21:18,611
She's wealthy, refined, and modest.

370
00:21:18,695 --> 00:21:22,448
I think Teo is still investigating it.

371
00:21:22,532 --> 00:21:25,284
That's why he's always lost
in his own thoughts.

372
00:21:25,952 --> 00:21:27,787
That's why he's always on edge.

373
00:21:28,663 --> 00:21:30,540
If ever...

374
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:32,375
you hear something,

375
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:33,835
give me an update, all right?

376
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:35,837
Okay.

377
00:21:48,474 --> 00:21:49,726
Ordonez.

378
00:21:49,809 --> 00:21:51,102
You have a visitor.

379
00:22:09,287 --> 00:22:10,663
Take a seat.

380
00:22:18,921 --> 00:22:19,964
Attorney.

381
00:22:20,048 --> 00:22:22,633
Why am I still stuck here?

382
00:22:22,717 --> 00:22:24,218
The judge said...

383
00:22:25,178 --> 00:22:27,346
he'd help me get out of here,

384
00:22:27,889 --> 00:22:29,432
as long as I kept quiet.

385
00:22:29,515 --> 00:22:31,601
I will be your lawyer.

386
00:22:32,185 --> 00:22:33,853
I already have a lawyer.

387
00:22:34,395 --> 00:22:35,605
The judge gave me one.

388
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:37,273
I will be your lawyer.

389
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:39,358
Why are you making it so hard

390
00:22:39,442 --> 00:22:41,360
for me to get out of here?

391
00:22:41,444 --> 00:22:43,613
Is this case even worth fighting?

392
00:22:44,697 --> 00:22:47,450
Why don't you guys just pay them off?

393
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:49,535
Why don't you just pay them off?

394
00:22:49,619 --> 00:22:51,704
Are you suggesting
I'm not capable of winning your case?

395
00:22:51,788 --> 00:22:53,873
It's not like that, Attorney.

396
00:22:53,956 --> 00:22:56,834
My life is in greater danger!

397
00:22:56,918 --> 00:23:00,546
You'll be in more danger
if you talk, Daniela.

398
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:05,301
Remember.

399
00:23:06,511 --> 00:23:09,013
We know where your family lives.

400
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:33,287
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

401
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:36,249
Congratulations, sir.

402
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:37,792
- Thank you.
- Another win.

403
00:23:38,835 --> 00:23:41,337
Governor Guevarra sent you something.

404
00:23:41,838 --> 00:23:43,506
A box of champagne.

405
00:23:45,967 --> 00:23:47,385
Nice.

406
00:23:48,261 --> 00:23:49,262
Send it home.

407
00:23:49,345 --> 00:23:51,347
And don't forget
to send him the bill, all right?

408
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,099
Congratulations.

409
00:23:57,353 --> 00:23:58,604
Thanks, Pa.

410
00:23:59,814 --> 00:24:01,774
You're coming here more often.

411
00:24:01,858 --> 00:24:03,818
I'm not visiting.

412
00:24:10,992 --> 00:24:13,077
I decided to work again.

413
00:24:13,161 --> 00:24:14,662
Effective today.

414
00:24:15,538 --> 00:24:17,957
I'm getting bored playing golf. And...

415
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:21,002
I didn't want to be an ambassador,
so I figured...

416
00:24:21,085 --> 00:24:24,422
I'll oversee the cases in my law firm.

417
00:24:26,382 --> 00:24:27,884
Is there a problem?

418
00:24:45,443 --> 00:24:47,695
I've been trying to catch you
at the right time.

419
00:24:47,778 --> 00:24:49,906
Must be nice to be rich, huh?

420
00:24:49,989 --> 00:24:51,115
I wonder...

421
00:24:52,116 --> 00:24:54,493
will we be stuck like this forever?

422
00:24:54,577 --> 00:24:59,457
- Why isn't anyone doing my touch-ups?
- As a servant? As a slave of some sort.

423
00:25:00,208 --> 00:25:02,501
You know what?
I'm actually confused.

424
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:04,212
I don't know what my job here is.

425
00:25:04,295 --> 00:25:06,839
All I know is I'm the madam's assistant.

426
00:25:06,923 --> 00:25:08,341
But she's asking me to do so many things,

427
00:25:08,424 --> 00:25:10,343
as if I'm one of her household staff.

428
00:25:12,261 --> 00:25:13,471
You like that, don't you?

429
00:25:14,639 --> 00:25:16,849
Besides, this is just for now
because of the event.

430
00:25:22,855 --> 00:25:24,857
Raya, move forward.

431
00:25:24,941 --> 00:25:26,734
Gem, kindly move forward too.

432
00:25:27,693 --> 00:25:29,070
And pose.

433
00:25:30,696 --> 00:25:32,448
Yeah, that's it. That's nice.

434
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:34,867
Gorgeous. I love it.

435
00:25:34,951 --> 00:25:37,703
Hold on. Why do they
have instructions, and I don't?

436
00:25:37,787 --> 00:25:39,747
Ma'am, you just have to sit there.

437
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:41,749
This is getting to be boring.

438
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:44,252
Let's take a break. Is the food ready?

439
00:25:44,335 --> 00:25:46,254
Uh, yes, madam. Um...

440
00:25:46,337 --> 00:25:47,672
Shrimp salad is ready, and soup.

441
00:25:47,755 --> 00:25:50,007
- Oh, good.
- Oh, thank God!

442
00:25:50,091 --> 00:25:52,426
- That's my favorite.
- Okay, let's go.

443
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:54,679
We'll also take your solo shots, ma'am.

444
00:25:54,762 --> 00:25:56,931
- Seriously?
- Yes, ma'am.

445
00:25:57,014 --> 00:25:58,266
Please, be seated.

446
00:25:58,349 --> 00:26:00,017
Okay! It's my time to shine.

447
00:26:00,393 --> 00:26:01,644
- Go, go, go!
- Take shots of her, okay?

448
00:27:02,455 --> 00:27:03,789
Thank you.

449
00:27:21,265 --> 00:27:22,475
Hey.

450
00:27:23,059 --> 00:27:26,520
You've been staring at her
since earlier. Why?

451
00:27:27,188 --> 00:27:28,230
Oh, come on.

452
00:27:28,314 --> 00:27:30,024
You're locked in, Teo.

453
00:27:30,107 --> 00:27:30,983
Don't even deny it.

454
00:27:31,067 --> 00:27:32,777
- It's so damn obvious.
- Larajean!

455
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:33,903
What is it?

456
00:27:33,986 --> 00:27:36,572
Is there something you're not telling me?

457
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,032
What do you know?

458
00:27:38,115 --> 00:27:39,575
This is about Yana.

459
00:27:39,658 --> 00:27:42,161
Let me guess, Papa told you

460
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:43,537
I suspect Gem and Yana
are the same person, huh?

461
00:27:43,621 --> 00:27:45,581
Hey, of course not!

462
00:27:45,664 --> 00:27:48,000
- I swear.
- Ronnie told me already.

463
00:27:48,751 --> 00:27:51,253
You're busted. Don't deny it.

464
00:27:51,337 --> 00:27:54,256
Larajean, Madam wants to see you.

465
00:28:00,763 --> 00:28:01,889
- Yes, Madam?
- Larajean,

466
00:28:01,972 --> 00:28:04,016
I'm just wondering,
what's my schedule next week?

467
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:06,560
- Okay, ma'am. Let me double-check.
- Okay.

468
00:29:19,925 --> 00:29:21,218
Love?

469
00:29:22,845 --> 00:29:24,096
Love?

470
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:28,726
Love?

471
00:29:32,771 --> 00:29:33,772
Love?

472
00:29:37,193 --> 00:29:38,110
Love, where are you?

473
00:29:39,862 --> 00:29:40,905
I'm here.

474
00:29:41,822 --> 00:29:42,823
Oh.

475
00:29:44,033 --> 00:29:46,076
But why are you here already?

476
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,912
I thought you were coming home late?

477
00:29:47,995 --> 00:29:49,914
I had to get out of the office.

478
00:29:49,997 --> 00:29:51,790
Dad is suffocating me.

479
00:29:51,874 --> 00:29:53,584
Self-proclaimed consultant
of our law firm?

480
00:29:53,667 --> 00:29:55,753
Why can't Dad
just trust me for once?

481
00:29:55,836 --> 00:29:57,421
Love, calm down.

482
00:29:58,464 --> 00:30:00,758
We'll be leaving for the US soon.

483
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,886
You can put up your own law firm there.

484
00:30:04,637 --> 00:30:06,597
No one's going to bother you.

485
00:30:16,982 --> 00:30:18,150
It's Josie.

486
00:30:18,234 --> 00:30:20,277
I have to go to the jewelry store.

487
00:30:20,361 --> 00:30:23,113
Wait, love. Sit down first.

488
00:30:25,741 --> 00:30:27,076
Can we just stay here?

489
00:30:28,244 --> 00:30:29,620
Or should we leave already?

490
00:30:29,703 --> 00:30:31,705
Get away from here.

491
00:30:32,456 --> 00:30:34,166
Maybe if we get rid of our stress,

492
00:30:34,875 --> 00:30:36,502
we can finally have a baby.

493
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:39,004
It's been three years now, love.

494
00:30:39,088 --> 00:30:42,049
Love, I know.

495
00:30:42,758 --> 00:30:45,344
But the doctors said
we're perfectly healthy.

496
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:50,432
And I'm sure we'll have a baby soon.

497
00:30:51,976 --> 00:30:53,269
But for now,

498
00:30:53,352 --> 00:30:55,604
we have to listen to Mama's demands.

499
00:30:55,688 --> 00:30:58,482
Remember, she might launch a world war.

500
00:30:59,567 --> 00:31:01,569
Is that what you want?

501
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:03,279
Okay.

502
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:04,905
Is there any food?

503
00:31:04,989 --> 00:31:06,198
- Yeah.
- I'm getting hungry.

504
00:32:01,629 --> 00:32:04,048
You've been avoiding me all day.

505
00:32:07,301 --> 00:32:09,386
Why didn't you tell me
about your suspicions?

506
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:13,057
I could've helped you with your mission.

507
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:18,354
Psst! Hey!

508
00:32:19,188 --> 00:32:20,981
Stop ignoring me!

509
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,611
I've done some research.

510
00:32:26,528 --> 00:32:27,946
I've also asked around.

511
00:32:28,906 --> 00:32:30,991
Yana died in Morocco a long time ago.

512
00:32:31,909 --> 00:32:33,786
There you go.

513
00:32:35,996 --> 00:32:38,290
The only way to be sure is

514
00:32:38,374 --> 00:32:43,712
to get her biometrics or run a DNA test.

515
00:32:43,796 --> 00:32:45,631
But you don't have a point of reference.

516
00:32:45,714 --> 00:32:47,675
So, what are you obsessing over?

517
00:32:48,842 --> 00:32:51,178
Nothing. Okay?

518
00:32:52,262 --> 00:32:54,682
Larajean, I'm here to work.

519
00:32:55,265 --> 00:32:56,350
To make a living.

520
00:32:57,393 --> 00:32:58,394
That's all.

521
00:33:01,605 --> 00:33:03,524
That stare said otherwise.

522
00:33:03,607 --> 00:33:06,276
You know what I think?

523
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:11,115
Your plan smells like vengeance
with karma on the side to me, Teo.

524
00:33:11,782 --> 00:33:12,950
Am I right?

525
00:33:14,827 --> 00:33:16,036
No.

526
00:33:17,329 --> 00:33:19,832
If I were to see Yana,

527
00:33:21,625 --> 00:33:23,836
I don't want to get revenge on her,

528
00:33:24,670 --> 00:33:25,713
I want justice.

529
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:28,048
That's all.

530
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:45,774
- Honk the horn.
- Yes, sir.

531
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:50,779
- Get out.
- Yes, sir.

532
00:33:58,328 --> 00:33:59,413
Wait for me here.

533
00:33:59,496 --> 00:34:00,873
Sir?

534
00:34:00,956 --> 00:34:02,541
Wait for me here!

535
00:34:31,820 --> 00:34:32,905
Good evening, boss.

536
00:34:45,959 --> 00:34:47,795
Bring out your passports.

537
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:05,187
Take their passports.

538
00:35:05,270 --> 00:35:07,356
Put our operations on hold.

539
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:10,776
And ask them
if anyone knows Daniela Ordonez.

540
00:35:11,401 --> 00:35:14,238
Maybe one of the recruits
is a friend of hers.

541
00:35:40,889 --> 00:35:42,266
Hey!

542
00:35:42,349 --> 00:35:43,892
What are you doing?

543
00:35:43,976 --> 00:35:45,936
- I... I'm a reporter.
- Huh?

544
00:35:46,895 --> 00:35:48,522
- I'm a reporter!
- Yeah, right.

545
00:35:48,605 --> 00:35:49,773
Come with me!

546
00:35:49,857 --> 00:35:51,233
- What the hell?
- Stop resisting!

547
00:35:51,316 --> 00:35:52,484
- I told you, I'm a reporter!
- Guard!

548
00:35:52,568 --> 00:35:54,736
- Guard, we have a thief!
- Check my ID!

549
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,905
I'm not a thief!

550
00:35:56,989 --> 00:35:59,283
- Guard!
- I'm a reporter, not a thief.

551
00:35:59,366 --> 00:36:00,492
What are you doing here?

552
00:36:01,118 --> 00:36:02,202
Don't move!

553
00:36:02,286 --> 00:36:03,787
- Call for backup.
- Okay.

554
00:36:08,125 --> 00:36:10,794
- What was that?
- We have a problem outside.

555
00:36:20,304 --> 00:36:21,638
Attorney Verona.

556
00:36:21,722 --> 00:36:23,223
My name is Hans Ruiz.

557
00:36:23,307 --> 00:36:24,766
I'm a reporter from Kidlat News.

558
00:36:24,850 --> 00:36:27,853
Your new driver saw him climbing the wall.

559
00:36:30,647 --> 00:36:32,900
Attorney? Attorney?

560
00:36:32,983 --> 00:36:34,610
Attorney, Attorney.

561
00:36:34,693 --> 00:36:36,320
Sir, I'm a reporter.

562
00:36:36,403 --> 00:36:39,448
Please. If I disappear,
people will look for me.

563
00:36:39,531 --> 00:36:41,408
That will only confirm the rumors
that you're a smuggler.

564
00:36:46,747 --> 00:36:49,249
This is a private property.

565
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:53,962
My family is doing nothing wrong.

566
00:36:55,797 --> 00:36:57,549
Take him down to the police station.

567
00:36:59,009 --> 00:37:01,887
I'm suing you
for trespassing and defamation.

568
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:03,555
And if you dare report it,

569
00:37:04,431 --> 00:37:06,642
I'll add libel and cyberlibel
to your charges.

570
00:37:07,601 --> 00:37:10,896
I'll bury you in lawsuits.

571
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:36,254
Boss, is there anything else
I can do for you?

572
00:37:42,219 --> 00:37:44,346
A lot of people are besmirching our name.

573
00:37:44,429 --> 00:37:47,391
The people Papa defeated in court,

574
00:37:47,474 --> 00:37:50,978
and now the ones I sent to jail,

575
00:37:51,061 --> 00:37:52,729
are all joining our list of enemies.

576
00:37:52,813 --> 00:37:54,773
Are you going to press charges
against that reporter?

577
00:37:54,856 --> 00:37:56,066
Of course!

578
00:37:56,733 --> 00:37:58,235
To teach him a lesson.

579
00:37:59,486 --> 00:38:01,613
There's nothing wrong
with the charges I'm filing against him.

580
00:38:03,657 --> 00:38:05,575
All right, you may go.

581
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:07,285
Okay, boss.

582
00:39:11,183 --> 00:39:12,601
Ma'am Gem?

583
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:15,520
Oh, it is you. What are you doing here?

584
00:39:15,604 --> 00:39:17,606
Getting some fresh air, obviously.

585
00:39:18,482 --> 00:39:19,357
You can go ahead.

586
00:39:19,941 --> 00:39:21,109
All right, ma'am.

587
00:41:21,354 --> 00:41:22,898
You're 20 minutes late.

588
00:41:22,981 --> 00:41:25,817
I had to meet my staff
about the new case, Pa.

589
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:30,197
You told me to prioritize the clients
before all else.

590
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:32,365
I know. I also know who it is.

591
00:41:33,408 --> 00:41:35,035
Daniela Ordonez.

592
00:41:35,911 --> 00:41:36,786
Drop the case.

593
00:41:36,870 --> 00:41:40,373
The court has ordered Ordonez to show up
and appear in court.

594
00:41:40,457 --> 00:41:42,292
And when that happens,

595
00:41:42,918 --> 00:41:46,004
your brilliant son will defend her.

596
00:41:55,263 --> 00:41:57,265
You're not handling this case.

597
00:41:58,225 --> 00:41:59,893
I assigned it to another lawyer.

598
00:41:59,976 --> 00:42:01,394
We can't get involved.

599
00:42:01,478 --> 00:42:02,687
Exactly, Pa.

600
00:42:03,438 --> 00:42:05,482
What if someone
convinces her to be a whistleblower?

601
00:42:06,608 --> 00:42:09,569
I'll handle the case
so I can watch over it.

602
00:42:09,653 --> 00:42:10,695
No.

603
00:42:11,696 --> 00:42:13,114
We can't take risks.

604
00:42:13,198 --> 00:42:14,908
Leave the case to me.

605
00:42:15,492 --> 00:42:16,993
Oh, by the way,

606
00:42:17,077 --> 00:42:18,703
I learned about what happened last night

607
00:42:18,787 --> 00:42:20,789
with that snooping reporter.

608
00:42:20,872 --> 00:42:22,499
It's a good thing Teo was there,

609
00:42:22,582 --> 00:42:25,001
or something else might have happened.

610
00:42:26,336 --> 00:42:27,754
Teo told you about that?

611
00:42:27,837 --> 00:42:28,838
No.

612
00:42:30,048 --> 00:42:32,175
The guards told me.

613
00:42:35,178 --> 00:42:37,472
If that reporter is presumed missing,

614
00:42:37,555 --> 00:42:39,683
we'll get in trouble.

615
00:42:39,766 --> 00:42:42,227
He didn't see anything last night.

616
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:44,271
So don't worry, okay?

617
00:42:44,354 --> 00:42:47,148
You take care of it.
That's your responsibility.

618
00:42:48,775 --> 00:42:51,444
I'll have our operations transferred

619
00:42:52,487 --> 00:42:54,906
since our location has been compromised.

620
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:04,582
You should go to the venue.

621
00:43:04,666 --> 00:43:06,501
Your mom has been nagging me about you.

622
00:43:08,545 --> 00:43:11,172
Let's have quality family time tonight.

623
00:43:34,237 --> 00:43:36,197
- Mr. Gani. Take a break.
- Yeah?

624
00:43:36,281 --> 00:43:37,365
Have some snacks first.

625
00:43:37,449 --> 00:43:39,409
- Okay.
- Come on.

626
00:43:40,660 --> 00:43:41,828
Let's eat.

627
00:43:41,911 --> 00:43:44,122
Oh, that looks good.

628
00:45:03,952 --> 00:45:05,870
- Divino.
- Hey! How are you?

629
00:45:05,954 --> 00:45:08,623
- Thank you for coming.
- Katarina, hello.

630
00:45:08,706 --> 00:45:10,041
Hi, Alberto!

631
00:45:10,125 --> 00:45:13,962
Katarina, congratulations!
This is something else.

632
00:45:14,045 --> 00:45:17,674
Thank you, Alberto.
And I love that you like it.

633
00:45:19,426 --> 00:45:21,094
What are you doing here?

634
00:45:22,303 --> 00:45:24,597
Were you invited, or are you gatecrashing?

635
00:45:26,724 --> 00:45:27,559
Pretty, isn't it?

636
00:45:27,642 --> 00:45:31,604
Does it suit me? Ma'am Gem gave it to me.

637
00:45:31,688 --> 00:45:33,731
You know, I looked it up online

638
00:45:33,815 --> 00:45:35,859
and a brand-new one costs 35,000 pesos!

639
00:45:35,942 --> 00:45:38,695
This is an upgrade to my wardrobe.

640
00:45:38,778 --> 00:45:40,822
- You talked to her?
- Yeah.

641
00:45:40,905 --> 00:45:43,450
Why wouldn't I? We don't have any issues.

642
00:45:43,533 --> 00:45:46,286
I believe she likes me.

643
00:45:46,870 --> 00:45:48,580
So, uhm...

644
00:45:48,663 --> 00:45:50,999
Are you ready? Shall we try again?

645
00:45:51,082 --> 00:45:53,251
Open your heart to me.

646
00:45:53,334 --> 00:45:55,795
You're just
putting yourself closer to her.

647
00:45:56,713 --> 00:45:57,964
Slight.

648
00:45:58,047 --> 00:46:00,717
But at least I get something from it.

649
00:46:01,426 --> 00:46:02,760
And yes, I admit.

650
00:46:02,844 --> 00:46:04,554
I want to know if you're right

651
00:46:04,637 --> 00:46:06,848
that Gem is Yana.

652
00:46:06,931 --> 00:46:08,057
Juicy.

653
00:46:08,141 --> 00:46:10,018
Larajean, let me handle this.

654
00:46:10,101 --> 00:46:14,522
Just tell me what I need to do
and I'll do it, okay?

655
00:46:15,482 --> 00:46:16,983
You're so stubborn.

656
00:46:21,029 --> 00:46:22,238
Thank you, Steven.

657
00:46:23,156 --> 00:46:24,824
I thought
everything had been planned.

658
00:46:24,908 --> 00:46:26,618
Why are you so anxious?

659
00:46:26,701 --> 00:46:28,828
Because your son isn't here yet.

660
00:46:28,912 --> 00:46:31,372
Excuse me, Madam, Sir.
They're on their way.

661
00:46:31,456 --> 00:46:34,042
Oh, finally.
Thank you, Josie!

662
00:46:34,709 --> 00:46:37,712
Well, here's one.
I think here's the waiter. Okay.

663
00:46:43,801 --> 00:46:45,470
Finally, here they are!

664
00:46:45,553 --> 00:46:46,554
Finally!

665
00:46:47,305 --> 00:46:49,641
Oh, here they are, here they are.

666
00:47:12,914 --> 00:47:14,999
Well, did you like it, Ma?

667
00:47:15,083 --> 00:47:16,751
Well, it's...

668
00:47:17,627 --> 00:47:19,754
breathtaking, I must say.

669
00:47:19,837 --> 00:47:21,047
I know.

670
00:47:22,131 --> 00:47:23,675
But honestly,

671
00:47:24,968 --> 00:47:28,137
had I known you were going
to make a quick change, Gem,

672
00:47:28,555 --> 00:47:32,392
I could've swung from the chandelier
for my entrance as well.

673
00:47:32,475 --> 00:47:35,144
Just for you.

674
00:47:35,728 --> 00:47:38,982
I agree, Mama. That would be entertaining.

675
00:47:39,065 --> 00:47:42,318
And I promise, the next time,

676
00:47:42,402 --> 00:47:44,821
I'll swing from the chandelier with you.

677
00:47:46,531 --> 00:47:48,992
- Really?
- Yeah.

678
00:47:51,703 --> 00:47:53,997
I've never been
to an event like this before.

679
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:55,707
Ronnie. Hey.

680
00:47:56,332 --> 00:47:58,001
Are rich people really like this?

681
00:47:59,627 --> 00:48:01,546
Are you really asking me that?

682
00:48:02,547 --> 00:48:03,631
Let's eat.

683
00:48:05,049 --> 00:48:06,634
- Let's eat, guys.
- Is this yours?

684
00:48:09,178 --> 00:48:10,179
There's more here.

685
00:48:10,263 --> 00:48:11,264
What are you doing here?

686
00:48:13,016 --> 00:48:14,767
- I was invited.
- Why?

687
00:48:14,851 --> 00:48:16,853
I am also a scholar of the Veronas,

688
00:48:16,936 --> 00:48:18,146
so I was invited with them.

689
00:48:18,855 --> 00:48:21,357
Oh well, it's nice to see you.

690
00:48:21,733 --> 00:48:23,735
Enjoy. Enjoy, guys.

691
00:48:24,235 --> 00:48:25,153
Let's go, Gracie.

692
00:48:25,987 --> 00:48:27,238
Does my outfit look bad?

693
00:48:27,697 --> 00:48:29,407
- It looks fine.
- Yeah.

694
00:48:30,533 --> 00:48:32,869
Fruity taste, and I'm telling you,

695
00:48:32,952 --> 00:48:34,037
no hangover.

696
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:35,538
- Teo.
- Sir.

697
00:48:35,622 --> 00:48:37,123
You're here.

698
00:48:37,206 --> 00:48:39,167
I need you to do something.
Go to Ma'am Gem's room

699
00:48:39,250 --> 00:48:41,753
and get the champagne bottles.
Bring them down here.

700
00:48:41,836 --> 00:48:42,837
Yes, sir.

701
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:11,843
- Here's the champagne.
- That was fast.

702
00:50:11,926 --> 00:50:15,096
And here's the room key.

703
00:50:15,179 --> 00:50:16,848
Thank you.
Thank you. Thank you.

704
00:50:20,143 --> 00:50:21,561
What's going on?

705
00:50:23,521 --> 00:50:24,939
Do you really want to help me?

706
00:50:25,690 --> 00:50:26,816
Of course.

707
00:50:33,740 --> 00:50:35,116
Hey, Ronnie!

708
00:50:36,075 --> 00:50:37,201
- Hi.
- So, you're a scholar

709
00:50:37,285 --> 00:50:38,286
sponsored by Raya's family.

710
00:50:38,369 --> 00:50:40,329
Such a small world.

711
00:50:40,413 --> 00:50:43,541
Y-Yeah, not just me.
Those guys over there, too.

712
00:50:43,624 --> 00:50:45,626
- Hi.
- Enjoying the night, Raya?

713
00:50:45,710 --> 00:50:46,836
Pa.

714
00:50:47,545 --> 00:50:48,755
And who's this?

715
00:50:48,838 --> 00:50:51,174
Uh, Dad. This is Ronnie.

716
00:50:51,257 --> 00:50:52,508
He's my schoolmate.

717
00:50:53,009 --> 00:50:55,428
We're in the same year,
but he's taking Legal Management.

718
00:50:55,511 --> 00:50:58,264
And also, he's one of our scholars.

719
00:50:58,347 --> 00:51:00,266
Ronnie, meet my papa.

720
00:51:00,349 --> 00:51:03,603
The... Judge Divino Verona.

721
00:51:03,686 --> 00:51:05,313
Good evening, sir.

722
00:51:07,398 --> 00:51:10,401
- Uh...
- T-This is mine, sir.

723
00:51:10,985 --> 00:51:12,195
Yeah.

724
00:51:13,404 --> 00:51:14,614
Behave.

725
00:51:16,073 --> 00:51:17,366
You don't have to do that.

726
00:51:17,450 --> 00:51:18,618
I can take care of myself.

727
00:51:18,701 --> 00:51:19,786
Raya.

728
00:51:20,536 --> 00:51:21,829
- Come.
- Ma.

729
00:51:21,913 --> 00:51:23,664
Have you met Harvey?

730
00:51:23,748 --> 00:51:24,707
- Hi.
- Hello.

731
00:51:24,791 --> 00:51:26,959
Why don't you spend
some time together and bond?

732
00:51:27,752 --> 00:51:29,420
Yes, Ma. I will.

733
00:51:29,504 --> 00:51:30,630
Okay.

734
00:52:01,661 --> 00:52:02,495
Ma'am Gem.

735
00:52:03,329 --> 00:52:05,039
You looked so stunning

736
00:52:05,122 --> 00:52:07,041
when you were making
your entrance earlier.

737
00:52:07,124 --> 00:52:08,793
How much is that, ma'am?

738
00:52:08,876 --> 00:52:10,461
It's my dream to have one.

739
00:52:10,545 --> 00:52:12,421
I'll definitely save up for it,
no matter how expensive it is.

740
00:52:12,505 --> 00:52:14,215
I'm determined to work hard

741
00:52:14,298 --> 00:52:16,926
so I can successfully do
what you did earlier.

742
00:52:17,009 --> 00:52:18,803
Actually, ma'am, here. Cheers.

743
00:52:20,805 --> 00:52:22,640
Larajean!

744
00:52:22,723 --> 00:52:25,852
I'm sorry, ma'am. I'm really sorry.

745
00:52:25,935 --> 00:52:28,020
I'm so clumsy.

746
00:52:28,104 --> 00:52:29,021
- Um...
- It's okay.

747
00:52:29,105 --> 00:52:30,106
I'll take you to the bathroom.

748
00:52:30,189 --> 00:52:31,023
No.

749
00:52:31,107 --> 00:52:32,191
- It's okay.
- I'll fix it, ma'am.

750
00:52:32,275 --> 00:52:33,526
It's okay.

751
00:52:34,193 --> 00:52:35,361
Accidents happen.

752
00:52:35,444 --> 00:52:36,737
I was going to change anyway.

753
00:52:36,821 --> 00:52:38,364
I'm really sorry, ma'am.

754
00:52:42,952 --> 00:52:44,370
"She's on her way there."

755
00:52:49,208 --> 00:52:50,459
"She's on her way there."

756
00:53:10,438 --> 00:53:14,275
What the hell
are you doing in here, you creep?

757
00:53:14,358 --> 00:53:17,737
I'll make sure they fire you after this.

758
00:53:17,820 --> 00:53:19,113
Sure.

759
00:53:20,406 --> 00:53:22,116
But before that happens,

760
00:53:22,992 --> 00:53:25,661
I'm going to tell your husband
who you really are.

761
00:53:27,330 --> 00:53:28,456
Yana Kassir.

762
00:53:31,792 --> 00:53:33,127
Oh, right.

763
00:53:34,962 --> 00:53:36,881
You aren't Yana either.

764
00:53:39,508 --> 00:53:43,596
Because you only stole
that identity, right?

765
00:53:47,266 --> 00:53:48,392
You're crazy.

766
00:53:48,476 --> 00:53:49,852
And this?

767
00:53:50,811 --> 00:53:52,229
This Gem Verona...

768
00:53:53,648 --> 00:53:56,192
Whose identity did you steal this time?

769
00:53:56,943 --> 00:53:58,986
How much did you pay Jorge Ybañez

770
00:53:59,070 --> 00:54:01,489
to cover up all the evidence
proving that you're Yana?

771
00:54:01,572 --> 00:54:04,867
What? Did you use
the money you stole in Morocco?

772
00:54:07,203 --> 00:54:09,622
You actually made up a whole story, huh?

773
00:54:10,957 --> 00:54:12,249
You really are crazy.

774
00:54:13,668 --> 00:54:14,877
Help! Ace!

775
00:54:15,878 --> 00:54:17,922
Ma, have you seen Gem?

776
00:54:18,005 --> 00:54:19,298
- Gem?
- Yeah.

777
00:54:19,382 --> 00:54:21,592
Oh, she's just around, mingling.

778
00:54:21,676 --> 00:54:24,095
She was just there earlier.

779
00:54:24,178 --> 00:54:26,222
Drop the act, Yana!

780
00:54:27,473 --> 00:54:29,058
Don't touch me.

781
00:54:33,729 --> 00:54:36,565
Teo, stop this.

782
00:54:37,525 --> 00:54:39,276
It's all nonsense.

783
00:54:39,360 --> 00:54:40,778
Nonsense?

784
00:54:43,114 --> 00:54:44,407
Teo, stop! Stop!

785
00:54:44,490 --> 00:54:45,574
This is all nonsense to you?

786
00:54:48,869 --> 00:54:50,121
You think this is nonsense?

787
00:54:50,705 --> 00:54:53,124
How about this one? Still nonsense?

788
00:54:55,251 --> 00:54:57,253
I gave this to you back in Morocco.

789
00:54:58,129 --> 00:54:59,338
When you manipulated me.

790
00:55:00,548 --> 00:55:02,967
When you set me up
so I'd end up in prison.

791
00:55:03,467 --> 00:55:06,137
You should've just died

792
00:55:06,220 --> 00:55:09,515
so I could get my family's life
back in order.

793
00:55:09,598 --> 00:55:12,018
You ruined our lives, Yana!

794
00:55:12,685 --> 00:55:14,437
Seeing you right now...

795
00:55:15,604 --> 00:55:18,232
you have no idea
how much pain you caused me!

796
00:55:26,157 --> 00:55:28,701
How many times do I have to tell you

797
00:55:28,784 --> 00:55:30,494
that I'm not that woman?

798
00:55:33,998 --> 00:55:36,333
What do you really want? Money?

799
00:55:37,835 --> 00:55:38,836
Money?

800
00:55:40,379 --> 00:55:41,589
Oh, yeah.

801
00:55:41,672 --> 00:55:45,468
You're loaded now,
living in the lap of luxury.

802
00:55:45,551 --> 00:55:47,470
You've got everything you wanted.

803
00:55:47,553 --> 00:55:50,765
Miss Nadia must be so proud of you.

804
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:54,643
Your Mama Nadia...

805
00:55:54,727 --> 00:55:56,729
the only person you can be real with.

806
00:56:09,742 --> 00:56:12,495
Don't you drag my mother into this.

807
00:56:15,956 --> 00:56:17,583
But she is not your mother.

808
00:56:18,834 --> 00:56:21,253
You aren't her daughter, are you?

809
00:56:21,337 --> 00:56:23,798
You were a fake then,
and you're still fake now!

810
00:56:23,881 --> 00:56:25,633
But your deceit ends here.

811
00:56:25,716 --> 00:56:27,968
Because I will tell everyone the truth.

812
00:56:28,052 --> 00:56:30,721
Wait... wait! What is it
that you really want, Teo?

813
00:56:30,805 --> 00:56:31,806
An explanation.

814
00:56:31,889 --> 00:56:33,307
Tell me the truth

815
00:56:33,390 --> 00:56:35,726
before I drag you
to your husband and his family

816
00:56:35,810 --> 00:56:37,311
and reveal your dirty secrets to them!

817
00:56:37,895 --> 00:56:41,524
Better yet,
I'll just tell everyone downstairs.

818
00:56:47,154 --> 00:56:48,364
No.

819
00:56:49,907 --> 00:56:51,742
You won't do that.

820
00:56:54,120 --> 00:56:55,704
Why not, huh?

821
00:56:56,747 --> 00:56:57,998
Why not?

822
00:56:58,541 --> 00:57:00,543
You think you can manipulate me again?

823
00:57:02,002 --> 00:57:04,421
You think so low of me, huh?

824
00:57:06,882 --> 00:57:08,634
Because life goes on, Teo.

825
00:57:10,094 --> 00:57:12,471
But only one thing is true.

826
00:57:15,933 --> 00:57:19,436
I had already dug my own grave...

827
00:57:22,022 --> 00:57:24,441
just so you could get out of prison.

828
00:57:29,363 --> 00:57:31,031
That was because of me.

829
00:57:38,164 --> 00:57:40,249
I had to die...

830
00:57:42,793 --> 00:57:44,461
so you could live.

831
00:58:01,395 --> 00:58:03,856
<i>Gem Verona</i>
<i>admitted that she is Yana.</i>

832
00:58:03,939 --> 00:58:05,232
<i>- </i>Then turn her in.
- What's that?

833
00:58:05,816 --> 00:58:08,569
<i>But what if everything we've heard</i>
<i>about the Veronas is true?</i>

834
00:58:08,652 --> 00:58:10,696
She's with their family now.
That'll put her in danger.

835
00:58:10,779 --> 00:58:12,740
<i>Teo, I hope</i>
<i>you don't throw your life away</i>

836
00:58:12,823 --> 00:58:14,366
<i>now that you are free.</i>

837
00:58:14,450 --> 00:58:15,409
Like what you're doing?

838
00:58:22,333 --> 00:58:24,293
<i> If you still have feelings</i>
<i>for that Gem,</i>

839
00:58:24,376 --> 00:58:25,878
it will only complicate things.

840
00:58:25,961 --> 00:58:27,671
<i>The Veronas are unforgiving.</i>

841
00:58:27,755 --> 00:58:30,716
<i>They'll make you pay</i>
<i>for the smallest mistake.</i>
